rles Stewart </b>believes can become a potential profit center. Likewise, m=
aking the Breuer building more accessible may also be linked to Stewart=E2=
=80=99s interest in generating revenue from a restaurant. The former uptown=
 home of the Whitney Museum =E2=80=9Chas a long history of successful resta=
urants,=E2=80=9D Stewart recently told <i>Vanity Fair</i>=E2=80=99s <b>Nate=
 Freeman</b>. =E2=80=9CWe will do our own take on that.=E2=80=9D   </li><br=
/><li><i>Who consigned Kai Althoff=E2=80=99s painting?</i>: I got a note fr=
om a keen market observer yesterday who wanted to alert me to the
