 the artist=E2=80=99s work with collectors in order to keep it off the auct=
ion market, so it=E2=80=99s a surprise that Schwartzman is not selling thro=
ugh her gallery. To further complicate matters, Schwartzman is a trustee ma=
naging the art that Gladstone left behind. Emails to
Schwartzman and Gladstone gallery were not returned. </li><br/><li><i>The s=
earch for Sarah Cunningham has ended</i>: Pleas for information about the w=
